</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Semi poll about the future of EQ and the 'changes'</span><hr size=1> VI made a poll about trivial-loot-code once and removed it, how about we show them what we think about the changes they made lately?<br>
<br>
1. Do you want NToV back like it was before the 'funny' patch?<br>
<br>
2. Do you want the Ring of Fire in Acrylia back like it was before?<br>
<br>
3. Do you think that perma-rooting mobs makes encounters trivial? Vulak, THO etc.<br>
<br>
4. Do you prefer the elements of strategy and personal skill over chaos and random outcomes?<br>
<br>
5. Do you think that the concept of deathtouch is a mistake in principle?<br>
<br>
6. Do you want VI to finish Bazaar as promised?<br>
<br>
7. Do you want VI to introduce the Luclin interface as promised?<br>
<br>
8. Do you want VI to test changes before introducing them to the game?<br>
<br>
9. Do you want VI to concentrate on quality assurance (90%) rather than expanding the game (10%)?<br>
<br>
Personally, I answered ALL of these questions with YES...how about you?<br>
<br>
Neric the Heretic<br>
~Mortalis~<br>
Antonius Bayle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unortherner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Northerner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/02 5:17:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23002.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Semi poll about the future of EQ and the 'changes'</span><hr size=1> 5: DT is a bad thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usmokingdorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Smoking Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/02 5:34:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23002.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Semi poll about the future of EQ and the 'changes'</span><hr size=1> 10. Do you think that the concept of extremely time consuming key quests abused in the Luclin expansion is a mistake?<br>
<br>
11. Do you think that overabusing of RoF type encounters just to force down the throat wasted time on raids is a horrid concept?<br>
<br>
12. Do you think that boss mobs droping random yard trash items (memory spheres, shissar fangs, etc) taking item slot is damn annoying?<br>
<br>
13. Do you think that making lots of triggered bosses despawn in a short period of time and not respawnin inmediatly cheapens this resource that used to be a flavor of really important bosses (aow) and just makes for another damn time eater?<br>
<br>
14. Do you think that the majority of Luclin bosses dropping just two items when most of the moon loot tables are loaded with garbage is a not fun way of stopping the good items to enter the world?<br>
<br>
15. Do you think that the whole master idea behind Luclin high end game (to increase by a factor of ten the amount of time required to have access to boss encounters / obtain good items) is starting to get right out annoying and makin Luclin a really boring and frustrating expansion?<br>
<br>
16. Do you think that the idea of no rent keys that must be camped each time the guild wants to face an encounter is just another forced time eater that makes guild resort to cheap game abuses to get around it?<br>
<br>
17. Do you wonder why lots of people prefer to do Velious for some straight boss mob killing fun instead of smashing themselves in long boring camps or doing the same encounters again and again (grimling war, seru praesertums -yay seru pathing-, commander farming, etc) bazilion times to get everyone in the guild a key?<br>
<br>
18. Do you cringe at the idea of what kind of an expansion PoP will be if its being designed by people whos main concern is to create time pitholes, forced downtime and bottlenecking spawns? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urolemeggido.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Role Meggido</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/02 5:35:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23002.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Semi poll about the future of EQ and the 'changes'</span><hr size=1> 1) The ring should be fixed or removed.  The current situation is quite <br>
2) Not as it was orginally but tuned a bit from where it is now.<br>
3) It definitely changes them.<br>
4) I don't understand the implied dicotomy.  Good strategy generally always helps.<br>
5) Yes, and it has not been incorporated into the game's expansions to my knowledge.  <br>
6) I would rather them finish the rest of Luclin and parts of Velious.  <br>
7) Yes.  VI's tendency to put things on boxes and then not actually produce them is quite worrysome.  Some might say it is almost false advertising.<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  hahah<br>
9) Yes.  Expansion is nice, however they risk everything by repeatedly turning out things that do not perform as expected and do not work.  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushandrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shandrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/02 5:59:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23002.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Semi poll about the future of EQ and the 'changes'</span><hr size=1> To clear up the strategy and skill over chaos and random outcome thing I need to go a bit into detail:<br>
<br>
Back in Vox and Nag days you had about 50 people (pickup raid /grin) guys charging a 32k hp mob. It was a plain zerg attack. If everyone did about 600 damage you would win. It usually ended up in a chaos, but someone usually survived and got the killshot in.<br>
Once they raised the hp cap a chaotic zerg attack was not possible anymore. You definitely need a strategy to kill the Vindicator for example.<br>
With Luclin VI did everything they could to introduce the element of chaos again. DT on maintanks, AE FD, AE charm, multiple lvl 60 adds during the fights, AE blindness .. whatever.<br>
So there is chaos again PLUS mobs have so much hps that they cannot be zerged. This is pushing us to the limits which is not bad in principle. We want such a challenge! On the other side, they surely pushed a bit too far in certain encounters like The Cursed or those rings where you have to fight 8 flurries or CH-mobs at once....<br>
Speaking for myself, I gain more pleasure from a well executed MT-strategy fight like AoW than from dealing with chaos in these rings or at The Cursed.<br>
<br>
N<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=anneli>Anneli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/02 6:11:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23002.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> **</span><hr size=1> 6.  Why?  With the implementation of the new chat channels- brell has instituted a channel called auction.  Hasnt replaced EC yet as the KMart of EQ, and not sure it will.  But the Auction channel means anyone in Norrath can buy and sell. <br>
